getting-started/requirements/.title: Requirements
getting-started/requirements/.body:
Requirements
There are a few basic requirements to run esys properly. This includes,

A laptop with an ethernet port and Windows 10/11
E-NET Cable 
5 Amp Battery Charger (it is possible without one, although if you own a BMW you can afford a harbor freight charger for peace of mind)
Patience

getting-started/requirements/compatible-.title: Compatible ENET Cables
getting-started/requirements/compatible-.body:
Compatible ENET Cables
There are a few enet cables on the market. 
Ebay / Amazon Cable1 ~$25 : These cables are common, although there are reports of slow transmission and quality issues. They aren't branded, and all likely come from the same factory.
MHD Adapter2 : This is what I use, and it is just the MHD adapter without the branding. Made in the same place with same QC, just without the stickers. There is an ethernet port at the bottom which you connect the computer to using a regular ethernet cable.

getting-started/software-installation/di.title: Disable Antivirus
getting-started/software-installation/di.body:
Disable Antivirus
Any antivirus including windows defender believes that the patching tool for esys is a virus. Windows believes the behavior of the program is malicious, however we intend for it to patch the software. This is NOT a virus.
How to disable windows defender : 
First, open the windows security app through the windows button : 


Next, navigate to the virus and threat protection window, then click manage settings :


From here, turn off real time Protection :

getting-started/software-installation/ge.title: Generating ESYS Token
getting-started/software-installation/ge.body:
Generating ESYS Token
First, open Token Generator. A window will open up stating it is malicious, but it is not. Click more info, then run.  Now, click save token and remember where it is saved.


Now, first open the esys launcher pro you had installed. Click the plus button on the side, and allow it to navigate to the default directory. If it didn't, you can use the one in the gif. Afterwards, click the 3 dots at the end of the est path button, and navigate to the documents folder and click the token. Then, type the pin from the TokenBuster into the launcher. 




Now you are able to click launch now, A window will open up for activation. Copy the request code from esyslauncher and paste it into the activation code box in TokenBuster. From here, copy the response code and paste it into the activation code box in esys launcher. Click activate, then click launch esys again.


After ESYS opens, click private networks, then allow access. In esys, click ok and you can close it.



You may need to repeat these steps in the future if esys resets.
Congrats! Esys is fully up and ready! Now we can install the PSDZ Data
